The general faculty consensus is that 127 helps to create context for 189's material, so taking it first helps.

---

127 is good preparation for 189. It teaches you how to formulate problems in the setting of LPs, quadratics, etc. and gives a lot of linear algebra/optimization maturity that the 189 profs (this semester at least) more or less take for granted. After 189 you could be pretty bored by it.
The general faculty consensus is that 127 helps to create context for 189's material, so taking it first helps.
